Text Splitters in LangChain – Compact Advanced Notes

1. What is Text Splitting

Text splitting = Breaking large text into smaller chunks for LLM processing.

Example:

Large PDF → Split → Small chunks → Embedding → Retrieval → LLM


⸻

2. Why Text Splitting is Needed

Main reasons:
	1.	Context limit
LLMs cannot take very large input.
	2.	Better embeddings
Small chunks capture meaning better.
	3.	Better retrieval
Search works better on small chunks.
	4.	Better summarization
Less hallucination.
	5.	Less computation
Smaller data = faster processing.

⸻

3. Types of Text Splitters

4 main types:

Type	Idea
Length based	Split by size
Text structure	Split by paragraph/sentence
Document structure	Split code/markdown
Semantic	Split by meaning


⸻

4. Length Based Splitting

Split by:
	•	Characters
	•	Tokens

Example:

Chunk size = 100

Text → 100 chars → Chunk1
Next 100 → Chunk2

Pros:
	•	Simple
	•	Fast

Cons:
	•	Breaks sentences
	•	Breaks meaning

⸻

5. Chunk Overlap

Chunk overlap = repeated text between chunks

Example:

Chunk size = 100
Overlap = 20

Chunk1 → 0–100

Chunk2 → 80–180

Why needed:

Prevents context loss.

Recommended:

10–20% of chunk size

Example:

Chunk size:
500

Overlap:
50–100

⸻

6. Recursive Character Text Splitter (Most Important)

Most used splitter.

Logic:

Split priority:

Paragraph

If large →

Sentence

If large →

Word

If large →

Character

Why best:

Maintains meaning better than character split.

⸻

7. Important Parameters

Two main parameters:

chunk_size

Size of each chunk.

Example:

chunk_size = 500


⸻

chunk_overlap

Repeated context.

Example:

chunk_overlap = 50


⸻

8. Important Functions

split_text()

Input:
String

chunks = splitter.split_text(text)


⸻

split_documents()

Input:
Document objects

chunks = splitter.split_documents(docs)

Used in RAG pipelines.

⸻

9. Best Default Configuration

Good starting values:

chunk_size = 500

chunk_overlap = 50

For big PDFs:

chunk_size = 800

chunk_overlap = 100


⸻

10. Where It Fits in RAG

Flow:

Document Loader
      ↓
Text Splitter
      ↓
Embedding
      ↓
Vector DB
      ↓
Retriever
      ↓
LLM

Text splitter always comes after loader.

⸻

